Impression: Interval removal of a double-lumen right internal jugular large-bore catheter. The heart remains mildly enlarged. Overall mediastinal contours are likely stable given patient rotation on the current study. Lung volumes are somewhat low with no focal airspace consolidation to suggest pneumonia. Some crowding of the perihilar vasculature, but no overt pulmonary edema. No effusions. No large pneumothorax.
